history.content: Afaik they are all evaluated at the same time after the application period closes. I declared in Spring 2020 and submitted my form relatively early (around 4/30 I believe) and my friend submitted his a lot later (near the deadline) and we both got our results at the same time.

Hi! So my summer CS70 grades are out but I wanted to fill the CS major petition over the weekend because I wanted to actually plan out my future CS classes that the form requires me to fill out. Although the petition form is due on 30th August, will the forms be processed on a first-come first-serve basis or will they all be processed only after the deadline? Basically, I fear that the space for CS major might run out if the forms are evaluated on a first-come first-serve basis even though I have the gpa to declare CS. Thanks!
history.subject: CS Petition Form First Come First Serve?
